Article_Name: Charanjit Channi Won't Be Elected MLA: Arvind Kejriwal's Telepoll Claim
News Info: Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal today claimed that Punjab Chief Minister Channi is losing from both seats he is contesting and this has been confirmed through another of their telepolls, which was repeated thrice.

Article_Name: Karnataka Hijab Row: No Mass Gatherings Around Schools In Udupi
News Info: The Udupi district administration has imposed prohibitory orders under Section 144 of CrPC in areas around all high schools in the district from Monday till February 19.

Article_Name: Goa Votes Tomorrow For 40 Assembly Seats
News Info: With campaigning for the 40 Assembly seats Goa concluding on Saturday, the state will go to polls in a single phase on Monday.

Article_Name: Uttarakhand, Known For Political Instability, Votes On Monday
News Info: Having seen 11 Chief Ministers in the last two decades since the formation of Uttarakhand, the hilly state will vote on Monday for its 70-member Assembly seats.

Article_Name: See Satellite Pics Of Massive Russian Forces' Build-Up Near Ukraine
News Info: Maxar satellite imagery of Russian deployments in Belarus, Crimea and western Russia show massive build-up of forces as tensions rise over a possible Russian invasion of Ukraine.

Article_Name: KCR Wants Himanta Sarma Sacked For "Father-Son" Barb At Rahul Gandhi
News Info: Telangana Chief Minister K Chandrashekar Rao has urged Prime Minister Narendra Modi and BJP chief Jagat Prakash Nadda to sack Assam Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma for his controversial remarks on Congress leader Rahul Gandhi.

Article_Name: Sarpanch Candidates In Odisha Appear For Entrance Test Before Rural Polls
News Info: Days ahead of the three-tier panchayat polls in Odisha, residents of a tribal-dominated village in Sundergarh district reportedly organised "oral and written entrance tests" for all the sarpanch candidates to boost their confidence.

Article_Name: World Radio Day 2022: Date, Theme, History And Significance Of World Radio Day
News Info: Every year, World Radio Day is celebrated on February 13 with an aim to underline the importance of radio.

Article_Name: Covid Reinfections Milder, Strengthen Immunity? What Experts Say
News Info: How common are reinfections? The UK has recently started publishing data on reinfections on its COVID dashboard. It classifies a reinfection as someone receiving a new positive COVID test result more than 90 days after their last infection.

Article_Name: Assam BJP Leader Alleges Conspiracy In Cousins' Deaths, Demands CBI Probe
News Info: Senior BJP leader and Lok Sabha member from Assam's Silchar Rajdeep Roy on Saturday demanded a CBI inquiry into the deaths of two cousins in neighbouring Mizoram, alleging a police cover-up.

Article_Name: Assembly Elections LIVE: PM Modi To Address Rallies In Uttar Pradesh, Punjab
News Info: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will address elections rallies in poll-bound Uttar Pradesh and Punjab today. The rallies are scheduled in Uttar Pradesh's Akbarpur and Punjab's Jalandar.

Article_Name: Pilot's Body Found 2 Weeks After Japan's Fighter Jet Vanished From Radar
News Info: Japan's airforce said Sunday that it had recovered the body of one of two crewmen of a fighter jet that went missing two weeks ago.

Article_Name: Punjab Chief Minister Says This To Arvind Kejriwal On Illegal Sand Mining
News Info: Charanjit Singh Channi has hit back at Aam Aadmi Party chief Arvind Kejriwal after the Punjab Chief Minister's name was cleared of allegations linked to illegal sand mining in his constituency ahead of voting day in the assembly elections.

Article_Name: Video: Woman Dangles Son By Saree From 10th Floor To Get Clothes From 9th
News Info: A woman living on the 10th floor of a Faridabad highrise dangled her son by a saree to drop him on the floor below so that he could get back clothes that fell there. She then pulled him back in the same way.

Article_Name: "Until The End": Canada's Anti-Covid Curbs' Protesters Dig Their Heels In
News Info: Feeling excluded from society and tired of Covid-19 restrictions, three Canadians protesting at the rallies that have paralyzed Ottawa said they had "nothing left to lose."
